# Scoreboard — Project Architecture

## Purpose

Beach tennis scoreboard application. Tracks points, games, sets and matches in real time following official beach tennis rules.

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Frontend framework | React 19 |
| Backend framework | NestJS 11 |
| Auth | Keycloak 26.5.6 (custom Docker image — `apps/auth/`) |
| Language | TypeScript 5.9 |
| Frontend build | Vite 8 |
| Mobile app | Expo SDK 54 · React Native 0.81 · [NativeWind](https://www.nativewind.dev/) v4 + Tailwind CSS 3 (`apps/mobile`, `@scoreboard/mobile`) |
| Backend build | NestJS CLI (webpack) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS 4 (`@tailwindcss/vite` plugin) |
| Routing | TanStack Router (code-based, `apps/frontend/src/router.tsx`) |
| Server state / HTTP cache | TanStack Query (`@tanstack/react-query`) — queries/mutations against the Nest API |
| HTTP client (backend) | axios (`apps/frontend/src/api/`) — base URL from `env.VITE_API_URL`, Bearer from `useAuth().token` |
| Client-side persistence | RxDB 16 + Dexie 4 (IndexedDB — matches, players offline / local cache) |
| API database | PostgreSQL + Prisma 7 (`apps/backend`) — migrations, `PrismaService`, generated client under `src/generated/prisma/` |
| Testing | Vitest 4 (frontend/core) · Jest 30 (backend) |
| Package manager | pnpm workspaces |
| Monorepo | Turborepo |
| CI/CD | GitHub Actions + release-it + Conventional Commits |

## Monorepo Structure

```
scoreboard/                     ← workspace root
├── apps/
│   ├── frontend/               ← Vite app (React + UI) (@scoreboard/frontend)
│   ├── mobile/                 ← Expo app (React Native) (@scoreboard/mobile)
│   ├── backend/                ← NestJS API (@scoreboard/backend)
│   └── auth/                   ← Custom Keycloak image (@scoreboard/auth)
├── packages/
│   ├── core/                   ← @scoreboard/core — DDD domain + application layer
│   └── shared/                 ← shared code (future)
├── turbo.json                  ← Turborepo task pipeline
└── pnpm-workspace.yaml         ← pnpm workspace declaration
```

Turborepo tasks (run from root): `dev`, `build`, `check-types`, `lint`, `test`.
The `build` and `check-types` scripts are **separate** so Turborepo can run them in parallel.

## Package: `@scoreboard/core` (`packages/core`)

Pure TypeScript — no React, no Vite, no Tailwind. Framework-agnostic domain and application layer.

```
packages/core/src/
├── domain/               ← Domain layer (pure, no framework dependencies)
│   ├── shared/           ← Base classes and shared types
│   ├── value-objects/    ← Immutable VOs (Team, MatchConfig)
│   ├── events/           ← Domain events (PointScored, GameWon, SetWon, MatchWon)
│   ├── point.entity.ts
│   ├── game.entity.ts
│   ├── set.entity.ts
│   └── match.aggregate.ts  ← Aggregate root
├── application/          ← Use cases (CQRS)
│   ├── shared/           ← ICommandHandler, IQueryHandler, MatchDto
│   ├── commands/         ← CreateMatch, StartMatch, ScorePoint
│   └── queries/          ← GetMatch → MatchDto
└── infrastructure/
    └── database/         ← Repository interfaces (ports)
        ├── match-repository.interface.ts
        └── player-repository.interface.ts
```

## App: `apps/frontend`

```
apps/frontend/src/
├── api/                  ← HTTP to NestJS: axios client (`http.ts`), resource modules (e.g. `player.ts`)
├── queries/              ← TanStack Query hooks (`usePlayerMe`, future mutations) — Bearer via `useAuth()`
├── infrastructure/
│   ├── env.ts                  ← Joi env validation — app crashes if envs are missing
│   ├── auth/
│   │   ├── keycloak.ts         ← Keycloak singleton (reads validated env)
│   │   ├── AuthContext.ts      ← React context + types (AuthUser, AuthContextValue)
│   │   └── KeycloakProvider.tsx ← AuthProvider — init, 3-layer token refresh, loading/error
│   └── persistence/            ← Concrete adapters (RxDB + IndexedDB)
│       ├── database.ts
│       ├── match.schema.ts
│       ├── match.serializer.ts
│       ├── rxdb-match.repository.ts
│       └── rxdb-player.repository.ts
├── hooks/                ← React custom hooks (bridge application → UI)
│   ├── useScoreboard.ts
│   └── useAuth.ts        ← Access auth context (user, roles, token, logout)
├── pages/                ← Route-level components (Login, Scoreboard, Players, Home)
├── main.tsx              ← AuthProvider → QueryClientProvider → RouterProvider
└── router.tsx            ← TanStack Router route tree
```

Imports from `@scoreboard/core` use the package alias (e.g. `import { Match } from '@scoreboard/core/domain/match.aggregate'`).

## App: `apps/mobile` (`@scoreboard/mobile`)

Expo SDK 54 + Expo Router + **NativeWind v4** (Tailwind CSS 3, `className` on `react-native` views). Config: `tailwind.config.js` (preset `nativewind/preset`), `global.css`, `babel.config.js` (`jsxImportSource: "nativewind"`), `metro.config.js` (`withNativeWind` + `input: ./global.css`), `nativewind-env.d.ts`; CSS imported from `app/_layout.tsx`. Web uses Metro (`app.json` → `expo.web.bundler: "metro"`). Direct dependency **`react-native-css-interop`** is required so pnpm can resolve `jsx-runtime` (see [NativeWind Expo install](https://www.nativewind.dev/docs/getting-started/installation)).

Part of the pnpm workspace and Turborepo pipeline (`dev`, `build` via `expo export -p web` → `dist/`, `check-types`, `lint`, `test`). Native binaries ship via **EAS** (`eas.json`, `app.json` → `extra.eas.projectId`). Versioning and GitHub Releases follow the same **release-it** pattern as frontend/backend (`apps/mobile/.release-it.json`, tag `@scoreboard/mobile@X.Y.Z`). Monorepo installs use **hoisted** `node_modules` (`pnpm-workspace.yaml` → `nodeLinker: hoisted`) per Expo guidance.

```
apps/mobile/
├── app/                   ← Expo Router routes
├── components/
├── global.css             ← Tailwind directives (NativeWind)
├── tailwind.config.js
├── metro.config.js
├── babel.config.js
├── app.json               ← Expo config (+ EAS projectId, experiments)
├── eas.json               ← EAS Build profiles
├── .release-it.json       ← release-it + conventional-changelog
└── CHANGELOG.md
```

### Environment variables (Joi validation)

All frontend env vars are validated at startup via `infrastructure/env.ts`. The app **crashes immediately** if a required variable is missing. Variables must be prefixed with `VITE_` (Vite convention). See `.env.example` for the template.

| Variable | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `VITE_KEYCLOAK_URL` | **yes** | Keycloak base URL |
| `VITE_KEYCLOAK_REALM` | **yes** | Keycloak realm name |
| `VITE_KEYCLOAK_CLIENT` | **yes** | Keycloak client ID |
| `VITE_API_URL` | **yes** | Base URL of the NestJS API (no trailing slash; e.g. `http://localhost:3000`). Inlined at build time; pass `VITE_API_URL` as a Docker `--build-arg` when building `apps/frontend/Dockerfile`. |

### Authentication (Keycloak)

Uses `keycloak-js` directly (no `@react-keycloak/web`). The `AuthProvider` wraps the entire app with `onLoad: 'login-required'` — no route renders before authentication. Token refresh uses three layers: proactive interval (60s), `onTokenExpired` callback, and `visibilitychange` listener. Use `useAuth()` hook to access user info, roles, **`token` (Bearer for API calls)**, and logout.

### Backend HTTP (NestJS)

- **`src/api/`** — axios instance with `baseURL` from `env.VITE_API_URL`; each request adds `Authorization: Bearer <Keycloak access token>`.
- **`src/queries/`** — TanStack Query hooks (e.g. `usePlayerMe` → `GET /players/me`). Prefer `enabled: Boolean(token)` so queries do not run without a token.
- **Providers** — `main.tsx`: `QueryClientProvider` wraps `RouterProvider` and sits inside `AuthProvider` so hooks can read `useAuth().token`.
- **API validation** — the Nest app (`apps/backend`) validates the same Bearer tokens using `nest-keycloak-connect` (`KeycloakConnectModule` + global guards). Env vars `KEYCLOAK_*` are validated with Joi at startup (see `.cursor/rules/backend.mdc`).

**Persistence split:** the **browser** uses RxDB/IndexedDB under `infrastructure/persistence/` for offline-capable match/player documents. The **Nest API** uses **PostgreSQL + Prisma** for authoritative player (and future) relational data. They are separate: REST + TanStack Query sync with the server; RxDB remains optional local storage.

## App: `apps/backend` (`@scoreboard/backend`)

NestJS 11 REST API. Imports `@scoreboard/core` via workspace dependency for access to the domain and application layer.

```
apps/backend/
├── prisma/
│   ├── schema.prisma      ← PostgreSQL models (e.g. Player), enums
│   └── migrations/        ← `prisma migrate` history (committed)
├── prisma.config.ts       ← Prisma 7 project config
└── src/
    ├── app.module.ts          ← Root NestJS module
    ├── app.controller.ts      ← Root controller
    ├── app.service.ts         ← Root service
    ├── auth/                  ← Keycloak: AuthModule, KeycloakConfigModule, KeycloakConfigService
    ├── config/                ← app, database, auth (+ Joi validation.schema)
    ├── prisma/                ← PrismaModule + PrismaService
    ├── generated/prisma/      ← Generated client (from `prisma generate`)
    ├── players/               ← Example feature module
    └── main.ts                ← Bootstrap — `enableShutdownHooks()` for Prisma disconnect
```

- `paths` in `tsconfig.json` resolve `@scoreboard/core/*` → `../../packages/core/src/*` for both type-checking and webpack build.
- `moduleNameMapper` in Jest config mirrors the same resolution for tests.
- Dockerfile at `apps/backend/Dockerfile` builds a minimal production image using `turbo prune`, copies `prisma/` into the runtime image, and runs **`prisma migrate deploy`** before `node dist/main.js` (see `backend.mdc`).

## App: `apps/auth` (`@scoreboard/auth`)

Custom Keycloak 26.5.6 Docker image with passwordless Email OTP authentication — **not a Node.js/TypeScript app**, not part of the pnpm workspace or Turborepo pipeline.

```
apps/auth/
├── Dockerfile              ← Production image (postgres, health, metrics, --optimized)
├── Dockerfile.local        ← Development image (start-dev mode)
├── VERSION                 ← Plain-text version (used by CI for git tags / GitHub Releases)
├── themes/                 ← FreeMarker login/account/email themes (future)
└── providers/              ← Java SPI JARs (future custom providers)
```

- Both `docker-compose.yml` (dev) and `docker-compose.prod.yml` build from `apps/auth/Dockerfile*`.
- **Bundled provider:** [keycloak-magic-link](https://github.com/p2-inc/keycloak-magic-link) v0.59 — downloaded from Maven Central via `ADD` in the Dockerfile. Provides Email OTP authenticator with auto-registration (`forceCreate`).
- **Email delivery:** Resend SMTP (`smtp.resend.com:587` + StartTLS). Configured per Realm in the Keycloak Admin Console.
- Future Java providers will be compiled with Maven and the resulting JARs copied into the image at build time.
- Versioned via `VERSION` file + git tags (`@scoreboard/auth@X.Y.Z`) + GitHub Releases — no release-it.

## CI/CD

GitHub Actions + release-it + Conventional Commits. Full details in `cicd.mdc`.

- `ci.yml` — commitlint + check-types + test + build (triggers on PRs)
- `release.yml` — CI + per-package release with path-based change detection (triggers on push to `main`)
- Commits follow `type(scope): description` — scopes: `core`, `frontend`, `backend`, `mobile`, `auth`, `shared`, `ci`, `deps`, `release`

## Key Architectural Decisions

1. **`@scoreboard/core` is framework-agnostic** — no React, no Vite, no Tailwind inside `packages/core/src/`.
2. **Aggregate root (`Match`) is the only public mutation surface** — call `match.start()` and `match.scorePoint()`. Never mutate inner entities directly.
3. **Domain events** are collected via `match.pullDomainEvents()` after each mutation and dispatched by the application layer.
4. **No parameter properties** in constructors — `erasableSyntaxOnly: true` in tsconfig. Use the Props pattern instead.
5. **Factory methods** (`Entity.create()`, `Entity.restore()`) replace `new Entity(...)` calls from outside the class.
6. **Tests live in `__tests__/`** folders at the same level as the file they test, inside `packages/core/src/`.
7. **Commits follow Conventional Commits** — use scoped commits (`feat(core):`, `fix(frontend):`, `feat(backend):`, `feat(mobile):`, `feat(auth):`) to trigger releases only for the affected package. See `cicd.mdc` for full details.
8. **Backend uses `paths` for core resolution** — `@scoreboard/core/*` is mapped to `../../packages/core/src/*` in `apps/backend/tsconfig.json`. This allows webpack and ts-node to resolve TypeScript source files without a compiled `dist/`. Jest uses the equivalent `moduleNameMapper`.
9. **Environment variables are validated at startup** — both backend (`@nestjs/config` + Joi) and frontend (`infrastructure/env.ts` + Joi) crash immediately with descriptive errors if required env vars are missing or invalid. Never read `import.meta.env` or `process.env` directly — import from the validated `env` module instead.
10. **Frontend auth uses `keycloak-js` directly** — no wrapper library. `AuthProvider` wraps the entire app with `onLoad: 'login-required'`. Use the `useAuth()` hook to access user info, roles, and logout.
11. **Frontend ↔ Nest API** — Use `env.VITE_API_URL` (never raw `import.meta.env`); axios in `src/api/` for transport; TanStack Query in `src/queries/` for server cache; send `Authorization: Bearer` with `useAuth().token` on every backend request. The backend validates tokens with Keycloak (`nest-keycloak-connect`); configure `KEYCLOAK_*` env vars (see `backend.mdc`).
12. **Where data lives** — Frontend: IndexedDB via RxDB. Backend API: PostgreSQL via Prisma; schema and migrations live in `apps/backend/prisma/`; production containers apply migrations at startup (`migrate deploy`).
13. **Mobile** — `@scoreboard/mobile` (Expo) lives under `apps/mobile`; participates in Turborepo (`pnpm build` exports web to `dist/`); native builds use **EAS**; releases use **release-it** with tags `@scoreboard/mobile@X.Y.Z` (see `cicd.mdc`).
